<p>A special form of the kite with four sides of equal length is the <a hre=
f=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/rhombus.php">rhombus</a>. Other special ki=
tes or deltoids are the <a href=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/60-90-120-de=
ltoid.php">60-90-120-90 deltoid</a>, the <a href=3D"https://rechneronline.d=
e/pi/half-square-kite.php">half square kite</a> and the <a href=3D"https://=
rechneronline.de/pi/right-kite.php">right kite</a>. The <a href=3D"https://=
rechneronline.de/pi/arrowhead-quadrilateral.php">arrowhead quadrilateral</a=
>, which is concave and not convex like the others mentioned, is sometimes =
counted as a kite. Kites form the side surfaces of the two Catalan bodies <=
a href=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/deltoidal-icositetrahedron.php">delto=
idal icositetrahedron</a> and <a href=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/deltoi=
dal-hexecontahedron.php">deltoidal hexecontahedron</a>.
The name of the kite comes from the kite play device, which is carried upwa=
rds by the wind hanging on a string and stands or can be moved in the air. =
These kites are often deltoid shaped and were originally made of fabric att=
ached to a wooden cross. The name Deltoid refers to the large ancient Greek=
 letter Delta =CE=94, which has the shape of a <a href=3D"https://rechneron=
line.de/pi/triangle.php">triangle</a>. The deltoid consists of two triangle=
s attached to each other.</p>
